news.title: Andhra Pradesh: Energy efficient housing tech training for 13,000 staff
news.para: The BEEP has come forward to conduct training on Eco-Niwas Samhitha to around 13,000 engineers/employees in housing department and village/ward secretariat departments in a phased manner.

news.title: Karnataka-RERA warns of action as 373 projects unfinished after deadline ends
news.para: However, while K-RERA plans to act against defaulting developers, realtors say hurdles caused by the pandemic was the reason for projects lying incomplete and want deadlines pushed back by another six months.

news.title: East Delhi civic body closes 44 out of 61 construction waste dumping sites
news.para: As per the instructions of the municipal commissioner, "the notified sites of dumping C&D waste has been squeezed from 61 to just 17", the East Delhi Municipal Corporation (EDMC) said in a statement.

news.title: Refrain from unscientific construction in sensitive areas: L Gopakumar, chairman, IIA
news.para: Gopakumar said that the IIA is ready to launch a strong campaign to build public opinion. “We will look at it as an opportunity to conduct environmental impact studies in collaboration with the state government and formulate a new design policy for Kerala.”

news.title: NGT: Ensure rainwater harvesting rules compliance under Punjab building bylaws
news.para: While disposing of the matter, the tribunal held that the statutory rules of Punjab acknowledge the requirement and implementation has to be ensured by the authorities along with the cooperation of citizens.

news.title: Developers deploy technology to make offices covid-safe
news.para: The report pointed out that developers are also taking steps such as renovating lobbies with more greenery, adding more shared event spaces and upgrading the hygiene standards of buildings to eliminate Covid fears.

news.title: Gurugram: Commercial power tariff worries Raheja Atharva residents
news.para: DHBVN has sent bills at a rate of 13.30 per unit. The residents say they are bearing the brunt of the developer’s “negligent attitude” in getting a domestic line even seven years after getting the possession.

news.title: Aditya Birla Group to set up paint unit in West Bengal, invest Rs 1,000 crore
news.para: The group has requested for allotment of land for a decorative paint unit with backward integration on 80 acres of land at Vidyasagar Park in Kharagpur, they said.

news.title: RBI issues draft directions to implement Basel III framework for AIFIs
news.para: ​The draft Master Direction, issued by the RBI, seeks to consolidate the existing guidelines on exposure norms, classification, valuation and operation of investment portfolio and resource raising norms issued to the AIFIs.

news.title: Government considering 5% quota for EV parking in existing buildings
news.para: Delhi Maintenance and Management of Parking Places Rules, which was notified in September 2019, makes the civic bodies responsible for arranging required parking space in areas under their jurisdiction, including preparing and implementing area parking plans, which require approval of the apex monitoring committee.

news.title: RBI to step up vigil with four-layered regulatory framework for NBFCs
news.para: According to RBI, Housing Finance Companies would continue to follow specific regulation on sensitive sector exposure, as are currently applicable. There shall be a ceiling of Rs 1 crore per borrower for financing subscription to Initial Public Offer (IPO).

news.title: Sebi confirms directions passed against 12 promoters of DHFL
news.para: In an interim order passed in September 2020, Sebi had restrained them from accessing securities market and had also barred them from associating themselves as directors or promoters of any listed public company or associating with any intermediary registered with Sebi.

news.title: Gurugram: Krrish World buyers protest against builders for denying them plots
news.para: According to some members of the Krrish Brahma Buyers’ Association, the project was launched in 2010 and comprises around 466 plots, many of which were allotted to them the same year. The project has been jointly developed by Krrish Realtech Pvt Ltd (KRPL) and Brahma City Pvt Ltd (BCPL), they said.

news.title: China's land sales slump for second month as property chill bites
news.para: The value of land sales nationwide fell 11.15% to 570.3 billion yuan ($89 billion) from a year earlier, according to Reuters calculations of finance ministry data released on Friday, after sinking 17.5% in August.

news.title: China Evergrande lines up funds to pay interest, avert default for now: Source
news.para: China's second-largest property developer sent $83.5 million to a Citibank trustee account on Thursday, the person with knowledge of the matter told Reuters, enabling it to pay interest on a U.S. dollar bond due by Oct. 23.
